  "texts": [
    "They represent different business goals as well as different ways and conditions of working.Despite data from previous technological transformations in support of net job creation and rise in efficiency, anxiety over mass unemployment refuses to disappear (Federal Ministry for Economic Affairs and Climate Action [FMEACA] 2022).",
    "Perception of job loss is not the same as reality (Dahlin 2022).",
    "Nonetheless, this is a very human reaction wrought by uncertainty.",
    "The adoption of new technology is considered a \"stressor,\" reducing short-term worker well-being and satisfaction (Gavin and Mason 2004); and although technology is an external, environmental factor, there is a limit to skill challenges workers can bear (Warr 2007).",
    "Some authors fear that digital technologies like artificial intelligence (AI), automation, robotics, cloud computing, and the Internet of Things would displace workers altogether or substantially and quickly reduce their need (Acemoglu and Autor 2011; Frey and Osborne 2017; Brynjolfsson and McAfee 2014), whereas others optimistically predict that there will be enough replacement jobs (Arntz et al. 2017)."
